summary: This is an email chain from July 11, 2019, between FBI personnel in New York, discussing coordination for a new victim interview scheduled for the next day at the SDNY (Southern District of New York) related to the Epstein case. The emails focus on arranging victim services and maintaining continuity of support.

persons.name: Min
persons.context: Addressed in the email chain; appears to be coordinating with other FBI personnel regarding meeting a new victim and her attorneys after an interview at SDNY.

events.title: New victim interview at SDNY
events.description: A new victim is scheduled to be interviewed at the Southern District of New York; FBI personnel are coordinating to offer services and meet with the victim and her attorneys.

keyFacts: A new victim in the Epstein case was being interviewed at SDNY on July 12, 2019.
FBI personnel in New York were coordinating to provide victim services and maintain established rapport.
The email chain indicates ongoing investigative activity and victim support coordination shortly before Epstein's arrest in July 2019.
